dct_title_s: Spain 1:14,000. Barcelona city plan. A.M.S. M981
dct_description_sm: Map shows military and coast guard headquarters. Some streets and buildings are named. "Iberian Peninsula zone grid (blue); Projection: Lambert Conical Orthomorphic; Spheroid: Hayford; Origin 40°N and 3°41'14.55"W; False co-ordinates: 600,000, meters east of origin, 530,000 meters North; Scale factor: Unity." Oriented with north toward the upper right. "Copied from a Spanish Map, 1:14,000, Plano de Barcelona; corrected from I.S.I.S. report 1:8,000; Barcelona, CB 1811 no. 22, 1942 and a Spanish Map, 1:25,000, Barcelona, 1935. "Army Map Service, U. S. Army, Washington, D. C. 114546. 1943. 3-43." Military grid. AMS 1. Alternate title: Barcelona city plan. Grid and projection approximate. Copied from a Spanish map, 1:14,000, Plano de Barcelona. Inset: City center plan.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1943.
